## Project Context

`src/events.js` defines `EventEngine` with a recurring-pulse + Poisson-draw scheduler. Tasks 4-6 added `_rollSilmarillionTier`, `_bumpSilmarillionVersion`, and `_fireSilmarillionRelease` (commits cdd1cff, 96da907, 65ebff9, 91fbfc9). This task wires those helpers into the engine's main loop via a new `modelRelease` pulse type.

The existing pulse types are `recurring` (Poisson-pool draw) and `fixed` (fires once on a specific day with a custom handler). The new `modelRelease` type runs the bump → roll → pool select → headline template → fire sequence via `_fireSilmarillionRelease`.

`MODEL_RELEASE_INTERVAL`, `MODEL_RELEASE_JITTER`, and `MODEL_RELEASE_OFFSET` are already in `src/config.js` (commit `ecef850`).

The events with `category: 'model_release'` don't exist yet — they're added in Task 8 (next task). So at this stage the pool will be empty and `_fireSilmarillionRelease` will warn-and-return-null. The `if (result)` guard prevents pushing null.

